metadata.name: Aweille! #128
metadata.description:
"Aweille!" is a small collection that I decided to put together in the last two hours of a single afternoon.

It is a study in exploration, accepting imperfection and delivering a project in a restrained timeframe.

I used noise and some really stretched out ellipse to create the composition. I also added some texturing to give it a bit of Oompf.

Hope you like it!

metadata.name: La Pedrera Serie 1 #216
metadata.description:
This project is inspired from Gaudí's Casa Milà in Barcelona, also known as La Pedrera. 

This is the first part of a 2-part-serie based on La Pedrera.

In this project, which is intentionaly saturated in color, you will recognize an abstract reproduction of the curved floors and windows of La Casa Milà.

The colors are accentued by the flowers disseminated on each floor. 

Main features of this project include:
- Palette: 10 colors,
- Texture: Strong or Soft,
- Noise: True or False,
- Strong Lines: True or False,
- Flower Packing: Mini or Maxi.

In live mode, press [s] to save a 1200 x 1500 (4 DPI) version of the mint.

Thanks a lot to everyone who will mint a token! :)

metadata.name: a square circle #18
metadata.description:
"It is impossible to make a square circle."
No human being, even if omniscient, could make this possible.
This may be a kind of sophistry.

However, we are in the opposite position.
"It is impossible to make a round circle."
The screen is always divided into squares.
We are merely looking at a polygon made of squares and conceiving the idea of a circle.
